<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-58-0368 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book begins with an overview of the current principles of geneticsand molecular genetics. Over this foundation, it adds detailed and specializedinformation: a description of the translation, transcription, expressionand regulation of DNA and RNA; a description of the manipulation of geneticmaterial via promoters, enhancers, and gene splicing; and a descriptionof cloning techniques, especially those for blood group genes. The lastchapter looks to the impact of molecular genetics on transfusion medicine.</TEXT></DOC>